Shush 16-Aug-17 03:18 PM
OK basically see how it works
you have a certain modifier that you got in some way, like a buff. Then, if you create illusions, AllowIllusionDuplicate() decides whether or not illusions should also get your buffs (edited)
however if you have a passive ability it means they gain their own buff
from the ability, and not from you
So GetIntrinsicModifierName basically grants illusion their own buff instead of "duplicating" yours
you just need to do OnCreated() if illusion then destroy return

UniBridge BOT 18-Aug-17 03:01 AM
<Perry> it's just the general difference
<Perry> initializers are only called on particle creation
<Perry> operators work the entire praticle lifetime
<Perry> so if you set for example radius from a CP in the initializer, you can set the CP when creating, but then when you try setting the same CP to a different value nothing will happen
<Perry> if you use the operator that will work
<Perry> because it's still doing its thang
